{"key":"post-15822931","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15822931</id>\n<content>If there's water left, you have plenty of water, so don't add any.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Always leave the weight off for the first ten minutes after steam begins to escape.&amp;nbsp; &lt;b&gt;If you fail to do this, you're building air pressure rather than steam pressure, and it's useless.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Once you have vented steam for ten minutes, place the weight on and allow pressure to build to 15 psi.&amp;nbsp; At that point, reduce your stove to the minimum setting which will maintain that pressure without excess wiggling of the weight.&amp;nbsp; You'll have to adjust the stove control several times during the process as required.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15823063</next>\n<prev>15822777</prev>\n<first>15822610</first>\n<last>15823063</last>\n<when>1329501771</when>\n<utime>02/17/12 08:02 PM</utime>\n</post>"}